#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an6.56"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.56:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.56:0.2"
msgid "6. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "6. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 56. Phaggunasutta → phagguṇasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an6.56:0.3"
msgid "56. Phaggunasutta "
msgstr "56. With Phagguṇa "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: phagguno → phagguṇo (bj, s1-3) | phegguno (mr)
msgctxt "an6.56:1.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā phagguno ābādhiko hoti dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Phagguṇa was sick, suffering, gravely ill. "

msgctxt "an6.56:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.56:1.3"
msgid "“āyasmā, bhante, phagguno ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr "“Sir, Venerable Phagguṇa is sick. "

msgctxt "an6.56:1.4"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā yenāyasmā phagguno tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Sir, please go to Venerable Phagguṇa out of compassion.” "

msgctxt "an6.56:1.5"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.56:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā phagguno tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to Venerable Phagguṇa. "

msgctxt "an6.56:1.7"
msgid "Addasā kho āyasmā phagguno bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. "
msgstr "Venerable Phagguṇa saw the Buddha coming off in the distance "

#. VAR: samadhosi → samañcosi (bj) | samañcopi (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.56:1.8"
msgid "Disvāna mañcake samadhosi. "
msgstr "and tried to rise on his cot. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.56:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ phaggunaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said to him, "

msgctxt "an6.56:1.10"
msgid "“alaṃ, phagguna, mā tvaṃ mañcake samadhosi. "
msgstr "“It’s all right, Phagguṇa, don’t get up. "

msgctxt "an6.56:1.11"
msgid "Santimāni āsanāni parehi paññattāni, tatthāhaṃ nisīdissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "There are some seats spread out by others, I will sit there.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.56:1.12"
msgid "Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane. "
msgstr "He sat on the seat spread out "

msgctxt "an6.56:1.13"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ phaggunaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said to Venerable Phagguṇa: "

#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an6.56:2.1"
msgid "“Kacci te, phagguna, khamanīyaṃ kacci yāpanīyaṃ? Kacci te dukkhā vedanā paṭikkamanti, no abhikkamanti; paṭikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no abhikkamo”ti? "
msgstr "“Phagguṇa, I hope you’re keeping well; I hope you’re alright. And I hope the pain is fading, not growing, that its fading is evident, not its growing.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.56:2.2"
msgid "“Na me, bhante, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti; abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr "“Sir, I’m not keeping well, I’m not alright. The pain is terrible and growing, not fading; its growing is evident, not its fading. "

# NOTE: abhimattha is used in the simile of the fire-sticks, where it can only mean “drill”.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.380, sc3
#. VAR: muddhani → muddhānaṃ (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: abhimattheyya → abhimatteyya (si) | abhimaṭṭheyya (s1-3)
#. VAR: muddhani → muddhānaṃ (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: ūhananti → hananti (bj, pts1) | ohananti (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.56:3.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, balavā puriso tiṇhena sikharena muddhani abhimattheyya; evamevaṃ kho me, bhante, adhimattā vātā muddhani ūhananti. "
msgstr "The winds piercing my head are so severe, it feels like a strong man drilling into my head with a sharp point. "

msgctxt "an6.56:3.2"
msgid "Na me, bhante, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti; abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr "I’m not keeping well. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an6.56:4.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, balavā puriso daḷhena varattakkhaṇḍena sīsaveṭhanaṃ dadeyya; evamevaṃ kho me, bhante, adhimattā sīse sīsavedanā. "
msgstr "The pain in my head is so severe, it feels like a strong man tightening a tough leather strap around my head. "

msgctxt "an6.56:4.2"
msgid "Na me, bhante, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti; abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr "I’m not keeping well. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an6.56:5.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, dakkho goghātako vā goghātakantevāsī vā tiṇhena govikantanena kucchiṃ parikanteyya; evamevaṃ kho me, bhante, adhimattā vātā kucchiṃ parikantanti. "
msgstr "The winds piercing my belly are so severe, it feels like a deft butcher or their apprentice is slicing my belly open with a meat cleaver. "

msgctxt "an6.56:5.2"
msgid "Na me, bhante, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti; abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo. "
msgstr "I’m not keeping well. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an6.56:6.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, dve balavanto purisā dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ nānābāhāsu gahetvā aṅgārakāsuyā santāpeyyuṃ samparitāpeyyuṃ; evamevaṃ kho me, bhante, adhimatto kāyasmiṃ ḍāho. "
msgstr "The burning in my body is so severe, it feels like two strong men grabbing a weaker man by the arms to burn and scorch him on a pit of glowing coals. "

msgctxt "an6.56:6.2"
msgid "Na me, bhante, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti; abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo”ti. "
msgstr "I’m not keeping well, I’m not alright. The pain is terrible and growing, not fading; its growing is evident, not its fading.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.56:6.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ phaggunaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired Venerable Phagguṇa with a Dhamma talk, after which he got up from his seat and left. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.381, sc7
msgctxt "an6.56:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā phagguno acirapakkantassa bhagavato kālamakāsi. "
msgstr "Not long after the Buddha left, Venerable Phagguṇa passed away. "

msgctxt "an6.56:7.2"
msgid "Tamhi cassa samaye maraṇakāle indriyāni vippasīdiṃsu. "
msgstr "At the time of his death, his faculties were bright and clear. "

msgctxt "an6.56:7.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him, "

msgctxt "an6.56:7.4"
msgid "“āyasmā, bhante, phagguno acirapakkantassa bhagavato kālamakāsi. "
msgstr "“Sir, soon after the Buddha left, Venerable Phagguṇa died. "

msgctxt "an6.56:7.5"
msgid "Tamhi cassa samaye maraṇakāle indriyāni vippasīdiṃsū”ti. "
msgstr "At the time of his death, his faculties were bright and clear.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
#. VAR: hānanda, phaggunassa → hānanda phagguṇassa (s1-3) | pheggunassa ānanda (mr)
msgctxt "an6.56:8.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ hānanda, phaggunassa bhikkhuno indriyāni na vippasīdissanti. "
msgstr "“And why shouldn’t his faculties be bright and clear? "

msgctxt "an6.56:8.2"
msgid "Phaggunassa, ānanda, bhikkhuno pañcahi orambhāgiyehi saṃyojanehi cittaṃ avimuttaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "The mendicant Phagguṇa’s mind was not freed from the five lower fetters. "

msgctxt "an6.56:8.3"
msgid "Tassa taṃ dhammadesanaṃ sutvā pañcahi orambhāgiyehi saṃyojanehi cittaṃ vimuttaṃ. "
msgstr "But when he heard that teaching his mind was freed from them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
#. VAR: dhammassavane → dhammasavaṇe (bj) | dhammasavane (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.56:9.1"
msgid "Chayime, ānanda, ānisaṃsā kālena dhammassavane kālena atthupaparikkhāya. "
msgstr "Ānanda, there are these six benefits to hearing the teaching at the right time and examining the meaning at the right time. "

msgctxt "an6.56:9.2"
msgid "Katame cha? "
msgstr "What six? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.56:9.3"
msgid "Idhānanda, bhikkhuno pañcahi orambhāgiyehi saṃyojanehi cittaṃ avimuttaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Firstly, take the case of a mendicant whose mind is not freed from the five lower fetters. "

msgctxt "an6.56:9.4"
msgid "So tamhi samaye maraṇakāle labhati tathāgataṃ dassanāya. "
msgstr "At the time of death they get to see the Realized One. "

msgctxt "an6.56:9.5"
msgid "Tassa tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti. "
msgstr "The Realized One teaches them Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. "

msgctxt "an6.56:9.6"
msgid "Tassa taṃ dhammadesanaṃ sutvā pañcahi orambhāgiyehi saṃyojanehi cittaṃ vimuccati. "
msgstr "When they hear that teaching their mind is freed from the five lower fetters. "

msgctxt "an6.56:9.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ, ānanda, paṭhamo ānisaṃso kālena dhammassavane. (1) "
msgstr "This is the first benefit of listening to the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an6.56:10.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno pañcahi orambhāgiyehi saṃyojanehi cittaṃ avimuttaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Next, take the case of another mendicant whose mind is not freed from the five lower fetters. "

#. VAR: na heva kho → no ca kho (mr)
msgctxt "an6.56:10.2"
msgid "So tamhi samaye maraṇakāle na heva kho labhati tathāgataṃ dassanāya, api ca kho tathāgatasāvakaṃ labhati dassanāya. "
msgstr "At the time of death they don’t get to see the Realized One, but they get to see a Realized One’s disciple. "

msgctxt "an6.56:10.3"
msgid "Tassa tathāgatasāvako dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti. "
msgstr "The Realized One’s disciple teaches them Dhamma … "

msgctxt "an6.56:10.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ dhammadesanaṃ sutvā pañcahi orambhāgiyehi saṃyojanehi cittaṃ vimuccati. "
msgstr "When they hear that teaching their mind is freed from the five lower fetters. "

msgctxt "an6.56:10.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ, ānanda, dutiyo ānisaṃso kālena dhammassavane. (2) "
msgstr "This is the second benefit of listening to the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.382, sc11
msgctxt "an6.56:11.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno pañcahi orambhāgiyehi saṃyojanehi cittaṃ avimuttaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Next, take the case of another mendicant whose mind is not freed from the five lower fetters. "

msgctxt "an6.56:11.2"
msgid "So tamhi samaye maraṇakāle na heva kho labhati tathāgataṃ dassanāya, napi tathāgatasāvakaṃ labhati dassanāya; "
msgstr "At the time of death they don’t get to see the Realized One, or to see a Realized One’s disciple. "

msgctxt "an6.56:11.3"
msgid "api ca kho yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ cetasā anuvitakketi anuvicāreti manasānupekkhati. "
msgstr "But they think about and consider the teaching in their heart, examining it with the mind as they learned and memorized it. "

msgctxt "an6.56:11.4"
msgid "Tassa yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ cetasā anuvitakkayato anuvicārayato manasānupekkhato pañcahi orambhāgiyehi saṃyojanehi cittaṃ vimuccati. "
msgstr "As they do so their mind is freed from the five lower fetters. "

msgctxt "an6.56:11.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ, ānanda, tatiyo ānisaṃso kālena atthupaparikkhāya. (3) "
msgstr "This is the third benefit of listening to the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an6.56:12.1"
msgid "Idhānanda, bhikkhuno pañcahi orambhāgiyehi saṃyojanehi cittaṃ vimuttaṃ hoti, anuttare ca kho upadhisaṅkhaye cittaṃ avimuttaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Next, take the case of a mendicant whose mind is freed from the five lower fetters, but not with the supreme ending of attachments. "

msgctxt "an6.56:12.2"
msgid "So tamhi samaye maraṇakāle labhati tathāgataṃ dassanāya. "
msgstr "At the time of death they get to see the Realized One. "

msgctxt "an6.56:12.3"
msgid "Tassa tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ … pe … brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti. "
msgstr "The Realized One teaches them Dhamma … "

msgctxt "an6.56:12.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ dhammadesanaṃ sutvā anuttare upadhisaṅkhaye cittaṃ vimuccati. "
msgstr "When they hear that teaching their mind is freed with the supreme ending of attachments. "

msgctxt "an6.56:12.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ, ānanda, catuttho ānisaṃso kālena dhammassavane. (4) "
msgstr "This is the fourth benefit of listening to the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an6.56:13.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno pañcahi orambhāgiyehi saṃyojanehi cittaṃ vimuttaṃ hoti, anuttare ca kho upadhisaṅkhaye cittaṃ avimuttaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Next, take the case of another mendicant whose mind is freed from the five lower fetters, but not with the supreme ending of attachments. "

msgctxt "an6.56:13.2"
msgid "So tamhi samaye maraṇakāle na heva kho labhati tathāgataṃ dassanāya, api ca kho tathāgatasāvakaṃ labhati dassanāya. "
msgstr "At the time of death they don’t get to see the Realized One, but they get to see a Realized One’s disciple. "

msgctxt "an6.56:13.3"
msgid "Tassa tathāgatasāvako dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ … pe … parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti. "
msgstr "The Realized One’s disciple teaches them Dhamma … "

msgctxt "an6.56:13.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ dhammadesanaṃ sutvā anuttare upadhisaṅkhaye cittaṃ vimuccati. "
msgstr "When they hear that teaching their mind is freed with the supreme ending of attachments. "

msgctxt "an6.56:13.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ, ānanda, pañcamo ānisaṃso kālena dhammassavane. (5) "
msgstr "This is the fifth benefit of listening to the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.383, sc14
msgctxt "an6.56:14.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno pañcahi orambhāgiyehi saṃyojanehi cittaṃ vimuttaṃ hoti, anuttare ca kho upadhisaṅkhaye cittaṃ avimuttaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Next, take the case of another mendicant whose mind is freed from the five lower fetters, but not with the supreme ending of attachments. "

msgctxt "an6.56:14.2"
msgid "So tamhi samaye maraṇakāle na heva kho labhati tathāgataṃ dassanāya, napi tathāgatasāvakaṃ labhati dassanāya; "
msgstr "At the time of death they don’t get to see the Realized One, or to see a Realized One’s disciple. "

msgctxt "an6.56:14.3"
msgid "api ca kho yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ cetasā anuvitakketi anuvicāreti manasānupekkhati. "
msgstr "But they think about and consider the teaching in their heart, examining it with the mind as they learned and memorized it. "

msgctxt "an6.56:14.4"
msgid "Tassa yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ cetasā anuvitakkayato anuvicārayato manasānupekkhato anuttare upadhisaṅkhaye cittaṃ vimuccati. "
msgstr "As they do so their mind is freed with the supreme ending of attachments. "

msgctxt "an6.56:14.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ, ānanda, chaṭṭho ānisaṃso kālena atthupaparikkhāya. (6) "
msgstr "This is the sixth benefit of listening to the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "an6.56:15.1"
msgid "Ime kho, ānanda, cha ānisaṃsā kālena dhammassavane kālena atthupaparikkhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "These are the six benefits to hearing the teaching at the right time and examining the meaning at the right time.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.56:15.2"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

